I can never overstate the importance of bipartisanship.

“People ask me what can be done to help me in D.C. I say don’t send another ideologue to Washington, send pragmatists. For institutions to work, the people who work in them need to work together.” https://www.jaxdailyrecord.com/article/u-s-rep-john-rutherford-ideologues-rule-d-c …

But to some communities, like rural districts with small police forces, school safety may mean an armed administrator or teacher in the classroom to immediately respond to a threat. I applaud @GovRonDeSantis for doing what's right for Florida's students.

State and local law enforcement and school districts must be allowed to decide how best to keep their students safe. When I was sheriff, I put school resource officers in our schools so that trained and armed officers could be ready if needed.

The goal police response time to a trauma event is 7 minutes. If an active shooter kills 5 people a minute, do we want 35 dead children before police can arrive? Trained, armed school personnel can be first responders before police get to the scene. https://www.foxnews.com/politics/florida-gov-desantis-signs-bill-letting-more-teachers-carry-guns-in-school …

Great news for veterans! Today my transition assistance legislation, the Veterans Armed for Success Act, passed @HouseVetAffairs as part of a larger bill and advances to the full House for a vote! This is a huge step towards easing the transition from military to civilian life.
#RamadanMubarak to our Muslim friends and neighbors as they begin a month-long fast. I wish all observing Ramadan a peaceful and blessed holiday spent with loved ones.
